<pre class='metadata'>
Title: Context Associations in RDF
Shortname: context-associations
Level: 1
Status: LD
ED: https://w3id.org/context-associations
Abstract:
  This specification defines a minimal RDF pattern for associating contextual information
  (e.g., provenance, policies, signatures, or other metadata) with a target RDF Graph by
  using named graphs as the unit of association. The pattern is designed for robust,
  best-effort processing when exchanging RDF datasets across ecosystem boundaries.
Markup Shorthands: markdown yes 
Boilerplate: logo no, conformance no, index no
</pre>

